title._content: Karl Franz Josef in Przemysl Fort  (LOC)

description._content: Bain News Service,, publisher. Karl Franz Josef in Przemysl Fort 1914 (date created or published later by Bain) 1 negative : glass ; 5 x 7 in. or smaller. Notes: Title and date from data provided by the Bain News Service on the negative. Photograph shows Karl Franz Joseph (Charles I of Austria) (1887-1922) visiting Przemysl Fortress, Przemysl, Austro-Hungarian Empire (now in Poland) during World War I. (Source: Flickr Commons project, 201s) Forms part of: George Grantham Bain Collection (Library of Congress). Subjects: World War, 1914-1918. Przemysl Fort Format: Glass negatives. Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication. Repository: Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division, Washington, D.C. 20540 USA, hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.print General information about the Bain Collection is available at hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.ggbain Higher resolution image is available (Persistent URL): hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ggbain.18143 Call Number: LC-B2- 3351-5
